      "id": "PopularPost302445",
      "post_content": "Its sad that Dwarves as a tribe got shafted time and time again. In Odyssey block they nearly made it with [Balthor the Stout](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Balthor the Stout) except he rewarded you for playing Barbarians, huh? He was a Barbarian lord not a dwarf lord. I understand the story that he was a mentor to both [Kamahl, Pit Fighter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kamahl, Pit Fighter) and [Jeska, Warrior Adept](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeska, Warrior Adept) But seriously couldn't they print him as other Warriors and Barbarians you control gain +1/+1 and First strike?  \n  \nBack to my point this is the perfect example of a Dwarf being undersized, given it was in Homelands and most of the cards in that set were very underwhelming by today's standard. But Wizards has yet to print a good dwarf creature because Goblins is the favorite red weenie tribe. Same goes for Elves, Zombies, Soldiers, and Wizards. ",
      "posted_by": "vantha",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost302445\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">Its sad that Dwarves as a tribe got shafted time and time again. In Odyssey block they nearly made it with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Balthor the Stout\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Balthor the Stout\">Balthor the Stout</a> except he rewarded you for playing Barbarians, huh? He was a Barbarian lord not a dwarf lord. I understand the story that he was a mentor to both <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Kamahl, Pit Fighter\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kamahl, Pit Fighter\">Kamahl, Pit Fighter</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Jeska, Warrior Adept\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeska, Warrior Adept\">Jeska, Warrior Adept</a> But seriously couldn't they print him as other Warriors and Barbarians you control gain +1/+1 and First strike?<br/><br/>Back to my point this is the perfect example of a Dwarf being undersized, given it was in Homelands and most of the cards in that set were very underwhelming by today's standard. But Wizards has yet to print a good dwarf creature because Goblins is the favorite red weenie tribe. Same goes for Elves, Zombies, Soldiers, and Wizards. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '302445'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                 